","value":"Yes! we are wired to do bad things too. I bet no one in this world who have not done anything bad to another life form - may it be animals, plants or other people. Most of the time we hurt the ones we so love. It is rather unfortunate and so depressing to admit that the people in the holocaust that shoot pregnant women at the back of their head are also of our species - they are also humans obviously.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":2125},"end":{"line":15,"column":405,"offset":2529}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":2125},"end":{"line":15,"column":405,"offset":2529}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"That is the point of the skill - embodiement of the shadow. As we navigate the world, we are always exposed to myriads of complex problems normally associating people to be dull or fall short of their responses to situations. We must fully accept our capabilities to which we can destroy others and control ourselves, knowing we can trap ourselves to the detriment of our own and harm of others. The control part is kind of tricky, also when trying to implement it with others. Being as truthful as possible to oneself is at the core of the skill, letting self-assessment be brutal as possible. Critically knowing how our capacity to destroy should be a priority - physically and emotionally. That is why I try to listen alot more than ever. Audiobooks and Podcasts have been tremendously helpful - the ratio of time for my listening as to talking could be 9:1 or 9.5 to .5. This ratio of consuming content is a vital source of clarity for me, enabling me to be more truthful to anyone I communicate and ground my arguments far better than the average person. Meditation is another invaluable way of establishing a better connection with myself spiritually - and I try to disect pressing problems through my meditation and normally getting bold solutions to them.  ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":2533},"end":{"line":17,"column":1266,"offset":3798}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":2533},"end":{"line":17,"column":1266,"offset":3798}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To combat monsters, one must become a monster and control themselves. The monster inside ourselves should be the one that we battle first, as it is a more effective way of tackling the much more larger challenges of life. This has proven to be one of my most treasured skills and I continually improve it in realworld settting. Moreover, it fits my ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":3802},"end":{"line":19,"column":350,"offset":4151}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://tech-stoic.github.io/stoic-philosophy/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"stoic paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":351,"offset":4152},"end":{"line":19,"column":365,"offset":4166}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":350,"offset":4151},"end":{"line":19,"column":414,"offset":4215}}},{"type":"text","value":" - my operating system of choice.","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":414,"offset":4215},"end":{"line":19,"column":447,"offset":4248}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":3802},"end":{"line":19,"column":447,"offset":4248}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I truly believe that no one can reach their fullest capabilities if they try to evade and refrain from combatting the shadow inside. Lastly, It is rather unfortunate that this was the case for most of history as most of the time where millions of deaths occured all over have failed to recognize the most important battle - the battle within.","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":4252},"end":{"line":21,"column":343,"offset":4594}}}],"position":{"st